commit.message: Removed lots of unneccessary info from envs.json

I cleaned out the form_steps.rb by finding steps that hadn't been
WebDriver'ed, and seeing if they were ever used, with commands like:

    grep -irn "I set the new \".*\" to something" features

I'll do each of these steps files, one at a time.
Fixed a route log verification step; now it refreshes if it needs to
Some helper functions and scripts; i dont use these a lot
Added lots of fun rake tasks
Cleanup, cleanup, everybody do your share!
Tweaks to get this working on toolkit
Simple Rakefile that doesn't do much. But it needs to.
Added a spec for file-name-safe strings
Cleaned up some stuff for video recording
Fixed incident report stuff for KATTS-734
Video now working, pcard_administration now working
Little source file for getting env up and running
Added some retry code to backdooring
Marked a scenario as incomplete; changed kdenman to csmith11; changed steps to refresh action list
Added ability to choose firefox profile, and firefox path
Tweaks enough to get KFSI-1021 very very stable
Removed show_complicated_tab as it didn't appear to be used anywhere
Added stuff about env, and headless
Adding actionpack and headless to Gemfile
Tweaking env.rb to use env variable; making new web_driver classes; using new wedriver select
Committing first commit after moving to new OS. No idea what these changes are.
Working on WebDriver support. I have a kaikifs webdriver class, and 3 kfsi's working
Removing commented code and unused methods
Adding some firebug helpers that i can quickly copy into the Firebug Console
Doing examples to help write scenarios in different ways
Added support for shared-password users, environments other than dev, and screenshotting
Added a buttload of step definitions
Adding screenshots and stderr to gitignore
